Speaker Yakubu Dogara has once again confirmed President Muhammadu Buhari’s health is getting better following his visit to the Nigeria House in London along with Sen. President Bukola Saraki.

The two lawmakers met Buhari on Thursday, and the photo ops were dhared on social media by Buhari’s media aide Femi Adesina.

Dogara said Buhari’s health has improved tremendously, and that he was glad seeing that the president is doing fine.

ALSO SEE: Saraki, Dogara back in London with Buhari

“Today we visited His Excellency, President @MBuhari. I am glad that he is doing well. His health has improved tremendously. @NGRPresident,” he stated in a tweet.

He urged Nigerians to continue praying for the president who has been on medical vacation for more than three months.

			
